FBIS3-28659 "dreas027_q_94003" FBIS-EAS-94-027 Document Type:Daily Report 9 Feb 1994 AUSTRALASIA Vanuatu Unions Extend General Strike BK0902065394 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 0500 GMT 9 Feb 94 BK0902065394 Melbourne Radio Australia Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] In Vanuatu, a 24-hour general strike has been extended indefinitely. Yesterday, Vanuatu Council of Trade Unions held a 24-hour stoppage in support of a 10-week old strike by public servants over a pay claim. The council's secretary, Ephraim Kalsakav, says the general strike was successful with most schools closing and government services disrupted. The airport was closed for several hours, delaying domestic and international travel. Scruffles broke out on picket lines with several people taken to hospital for minor injuries. Mr. Kalsakav said the strike would continue indefinetly until the government reopens negotiations with public servants.
